In '''''Compass Motors Industries (Pty) Ltd v. Callguard (Pty) Ltd''''', an important case in [[Law of South Africa|South African law]], Van Zyl, [[judge|J.]] expressed the [[Opinion (law)|opinion]], ''obiter'', that a [[Security guard|security firm]] that had contracted to guard a premises had a [[legal duty]] to third parties to guard [[vehicle]]s lawfully parked on the [[premises]].
